com.cmput301f19t09.vibes.fragments.profilefragment

Class ProfileFragment

  • java.lang.Object
    • androidx.fragment.app.Fragment
      • com.cmput301f19t09.vibes.fragments.profilefragment.ProfileFragment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.view.View.OnCreateContextMenuListener, androidx.lifecycle.LifecycleOwner, androidx.lifecycle.ViewModelStoreOwner, androidx.savedstate.SavedStateRegistryOwner, java.util.Observer

    public class ProfileFragment
extends androidx.fragment.app.Fragment
implements java.util.Observer
    ProfileFragment contains information about the the current user logged in or information of other users being viewed based on whether you're following the other user or not. Calls a child fragment to view user's own mood history if on own user profile but calls a child fragment to view other user's most recent mood event if following

    Following other users not implemented yet
